        <div class="text-sm text-primary font-medium mb-4">June 12, 2025</div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold font-playfair text-darktext mb-6">Can I Wear Makeup with Lash Extensions?</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-mediumtext">Yes, you can wear makeup with lash extensions! Just follow these guidelines for safe application and removal.</p>
      </header>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>One of the most common questions our Orange County clients ask is whether they can wear makeup with lash extensions. The answer is absolutely yes - with the right products and techniques. In fact, many clients find they need much less eye makeup with their beautiful extensions. Here's your complete guide to makeup and lash extensions.</p>

        <h2>Makeup Dos and Don'ts</h2>

        <h3>DO: Use Oil-Free Products Around Eyes</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Check ingredient lists carefully for any oils</li>
          <li>Oil-free eyeshadows work perfectly with extensions</li>
          <li>Water-based eyeliners are safe</li>
          <li>Powder products generally safer than creams</li>
          <li>Oil-free primers won't affect adhesive</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>DON'T: Use Waterproof Mascara on Extensions</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Waterproof formulas require oil-based removal</li>
          <li>Oil breaks down lash extension adhesive</li>
          <li>Extremely difficult to remove without damage</li>
          <li>Can cause clumping and premature shedding</li>
          <li>Honestly, you don't need mascara with extensions!</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>DO: Remove Makeup Gently with Approved Cleanser</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Use only oil-free makeup removers</li>
          <li>Pat and press gently, never rub or pull</li>
          <li>Use cotton pads or microfiber cloths</li>
          <li>Follow with lash-safe cleanser</li>
          <li>Remove all traces before bed</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>DON'T: Use Oil-Based Makeup Removers</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Even "safe" oils break down adhesive</li>
          <li>Coconut oil, argan oil, mineral oil all problematic</li>
          <li>Micellar water must be oil-free formulation</li>
          <li>Check even "natural" products for oils</li>
          <li>When in doubt, ask your Orange County lash artist</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>DO: Apply Eyeshadow Carefully</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Use gentle application techniques</li>
          <li>Avoid pressing on lash line</li>
          <li>Powder shadows work best</li>
          <li>Keep brushes away from lash adhesive bonds</li>
          <li>Blend outward and upward, not into lashes</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Safe Makeup Products for Lash Extensions</h2>

        <h3>Eyeshadow</h3>
        <p>Most eyeshadows are safe for extensions:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Powder shadows:</strong> Safest option, easy removal</li>
          <li><strong>Pressed shadows:</strong> Work well, minimal fallout</li>
          <li><strong>Cream shadows:</strong> Check for oil content first</li>
          <li><strong>Liquid shadows:</strong> Verify oil-free formula</li>
          <li><strong>Application:</strong> Use light hand near lash line</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Eyeliner</h3>
        <p>Choose appropriate formulas and application:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Gel liner:</strong> Oil-free formulas work great</li>
          <li><strong>Pencil liner:</strong> Avoid tugging on lash line</li>
          <li><strong>Liquid liner:</strong> Water-based formulas safe</li>
          <li><strong>Application tip:</strong> Line above lash line, not at base</li>
          <li><strong>Removal:</strong> Use oil-free remover with gentle pressure</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Mascara (If You Must)</h3>
        <p>Generally unnecessary, but if needed:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Water-based only:</strong> Never waterproof formulas</li>
          <li><strong>Extension-safe brands:</strong> Specifically formulated</li>
          <li><strong>Tips only:</strong> Apply to extension tips, not base</li>
          <li><strong>Light coat:</strong> One thin layer maximum</li>
          <li><strong>Daily removal:</strong> Must remove completely each night</li>
          <li><strong>Honestly:</strong> Most Orange County clients skip mascara entirely</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Face Products to Watch</h3>
        <p>Products that can migrate to lash area:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Foundation:</strong> Keep away from lash line</li>
          <li><strong>Concealer:</strong> Don't apply too close to extensions</li>
          <li><strong>Moisturizer:</strong> Oil-free around eyes essential</li>
          <li><strong>Sunscreen:</strong> Apply carefully to avoid lashes</li>
          <li><strong>Setting spray:</strong> Close eyes and avoid direct spray on lashes</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Application Techniques</h2>

        <h3>Eyeshadow Application</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Start with eye primer (oil-free)</li>
          <li>Apply base shadow across lid</li>
          <li>Use gentle pressure with brushes</li>
          <li>Blend away from lash line</li>
          <li>Avoid dragging brushes through lashes</li>
          <li>Clean brushes regularly to remove oils</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Eyeliner Application</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Line slightly above natural lash line</li>
          <li>Don't draw on the base where extensions attach</li>
          <li>Use short, light strokes</li>
          <li>Winged liner works beautifully with extensions</li>
          <li>Keep liner thin at inner corners</li>
          <li>Set with matching eyeshadow if desired</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Complete Eye Look with Extensions</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Prime eyelids with oil-free primer</li>
          <li>Apply eyeshadow as desired</li>
          <li>Add eyeliner above lash line</li>
          <li>Skip mascara - your lashes already look amazing!</li>
          <li>Highlight brow bone and inner corners</li>
          <li>Set with oil-free setting spray if needed</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Makeup Removal Process</h2>

        <h3>Evening Removal Routine</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Step 1:</strong> Remove eye makeup with oil-free remover on cotton pad</li>
          <li><strong>Step 2:</strong> Gently press and hold on closed eye (don't rub)</li>
          <li><strong>Step 3:</strong> Use cotton swab for precise liner removal</li>
          <li><strong>Step 4:</strong> Cleanse lashes with lash-safe cleanser</li>
          <li><strong>Step 5:</strong> Rinse thoroughly with lukewarm water</li>
          <li><strong>Step 6:</strong> Pat dry gently with lint-free cloth</li>
          <li><strong>Step 7:</strong> Brush through with clean spoolie once dry</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Makeup Remover Options</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Oil-free micellar water:</strong> Gentle and effective</li>
          <li><strong>Dual-phase removers:</strong> Verify oil-free formula</li>
          <li><strong>Foam cleansers:</strong> Work well for eye area</li>
          <li><strong>Lash extension-specific removers:</strong> Safest option</li>
          <li><strong>Available:</strong> At your Orange County lash salon</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Products to Completely Avoid</h2>

        <h3>Ingredient Red Flags</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Coconut oil</li>
          <li>Mineral oil</li>
          <li>Argan oil</li>
          <li>Jojoba oil</li>
          <li>Any oil-based ingredients</li>
          <li>Glycols in high concentrations</li>
          <li>Heavy waxes and emollients</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Product Types to Avoid</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Oil-based makeup removers</li>
          <li>Waterproof mascara</li>
          <li>Oil-based eyeliners</li>
          <li>Heavy cream eyeshadows with oils</li>
          <li>Makeup removing wipes (often contain oil)</li>
          <li>Cold cream cleansers</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Minimalist Makeup Approach</h2>

        <h3>The Extension Advantage</h3>
        <p>Many clients discover they need much less makeup:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>No mascara needed saves time and money</li>
          <li>Natural lashes look enhanced without product</li>
          <li>Quicker morning routine</li>
          <li>Less makeup removal needed</li>
          <li>Reduced exposure to potentially problematic products</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Simple Orange County Look</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Skip all eye makeup - let lashes be the star</li>
          <li>Add light eyeshadow for special occasions only</li>
          <li>Eyeliner optional for evening looks</li>
          <li>Focus on skincare and complexion products</li>
          <li>Perfect for active Southern California lifestyle</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Special Occasion Makeup</h2>

        <h3>Professional Makeup Artist Coordination</h3>
        <p>If hiring a makeup artist:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Inform them about your lash extensions</li>
          <li>Bring your oil-free products</li>
          <li>Request they avoid mascara</li>
          <li>Ask them to be gentle around eye area</li>
          <li>Provide your lash-safe makeup remover</li>
          <li>Many Orange County MUAs are extension-experienced</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Wedding Day Makeup</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Trial run with makeup artist beforehand</li>
          <li>Discuss lash extensions during consultation</li>
          <li>Bring approved products to trial and wedding</li>
          <li>No mascara needed with proper extension timing</li>
          <li>Focus on longevity with oil-free formulas</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Troubleshooting Makeup Issues</h2>

        <h3>If You Experience Premature Shedding</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Review all eye makeup products for oil content</li>
          <li>Check face products that might migrate to lashes</li>
          <li>Ensure complete makeup removal each night</li>
          <li>Consider simplifying routine temporarily</li>
          <li>Consult Orange County lash artist for product audit</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>If Makeup Gets on Extensions</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Clean immediately with lash cleanser</li>
          <li>Don't let products dry on extensions</li>
          <li>Use gentle dabbing motions to remove</li>
          <li>Avoid rubbing or pulling</li>
          <li>Better prevention: careful application</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>If You Forget and Use Wrong Product</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Remove immediately with oil-free cleanser</li>
          <li>Cleanse lashes thoroughly</li>
          <li>Schedule fill appointment if significant exposure</li>
          <li>Document which product caused issue</li>
          <li>Return to approved products only</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Building Your Extension-Safe Makeup Kit</h2>

        <h3>Essential Items</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Oil-free makeup remover</li>
          <li>Lash extension cleanser</li>
          <li>Oil-free eyeshadow palette</li>
          <li>Water-based eyeliner (optional)</li>
          <li>Clean application brushes</li>
          <li>Cotton pads and swabs</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Product Shopping Tips</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Read ingredient lists carefully</li>
          <li>Look for "oil-free" labels</li>
          <li>Check with your lash artist for recommendations</li>
          <li>Test new products on hand before using near eyes</li>
          <li>Keep receipts in case products need to be returned</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <h3>Can I wear mascara on bottom lashes?</h3>
        <p>Yes, but be careful:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Water-based mascara only</li>
          <li>Avoid getting product on upper extensions</li>
          <li>Remove completely each night</li>
          <li>Consider extension tinting for bottom lashes instead</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What about eyeshadow primer?</h3>
        <p>Yes, with precautions:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Must be oil-free formula</li>
          <li>Keep away from lash line</li>
          <li>Apply to lid only, not near extensions</li>
          <li>Remove thoroughly each evening</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Can I use setting spray?</h3>
        <p>Yes, carefully:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Close eyes when spraying</li>
          <li>Hold bottle at distance</li>
          <li>Oil-free formulas only</li>
          <li>Don't spray directly at extensions</li>
          <li>Fan to dry, don't touch lashes</li>
        </ul>

